description.text: Looking for a summer in Europe, but can't leave the city? Look no further than this 1930s Spanish jewel-box that will transport you straight to the South of France! Oozing with old world vintage charm and nestled on a tree-lined street in the coveted North Inglewood neighborhood, this home has been meticulously preserved to showcase its original character while boasting beautiful curb appeal. Upon entry you are greeted with a spacious outdoor courtyard perfect for morning tea or coffee while the interior of the home showcases vaulted ceilings, original hardwood floors, charming vintage tiles and french windows casting tons of natural light, beautiful greenery and gentle ocean breezes, bringing a refreshing touch of coastal living to each room! 3 spacious bedrooms and a brand new bath featuring a deep soaking tub is perfect to unwind and escape the stresses of everyday life. The enchantment continues outdoors with a spacious deck to lounge and the eye swoon scenery of dreamy Spanish architecture, lush greenery and an outdoor pergola wrapped with Concord grape arbor vines original from the 1930s. A perfect space to dine al' fresco while soaking in the idyllic surroundings.
